<br>
When a guild gets onto a rotation, it is not acceptable for another guild to go in after they are done and clean up what is left. any guild caught doing so will be assessed the penalty of losing their current rot turn and next rot turn on said rotation if they are not on said rotation a suitable punishment will be worked out on a case by case basis.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I believe this rule actually refers to going in after the guild on rotation has completed thier first day, and before they have started their second day.  The rule is in place because of ther different timezones guilds have, which could mean the raid time of two guilds would not overlap at all.<br>
<br>
There is also the fact that if Guild A kills say 8 of the mobs in NToV, but leaves the rest up.  Guild B should not go in 3 days later to kill the rest, because it would throw the respawn of the &quot;raid entity&quot;, which is all those mobs off.  I.E.  8 of the mobs would spawn on Monday, but the rest would not respawn until Thursday.  This would delay the rotation because most people do not begin a rotation turn until all the mobs within that rotation have respawned.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Rule: -- On mulptiple day zones (including, but restricted to: NToV, VT), if a guild leaves said zone to kill another Rotation Mob, their turn in that zone ends.<br>
<br>
Again, why? If we are in Ntov, kill half the mobs, decide to dispatch Dain real quick, go straight back to ToV (all within out allotted time for the rotation), why should we lose the rot? Doesn't make sense to me.<br>
<br>
Does this mean that of we have Ntov on Saturday and Sunday, and we are fighting in ToV on Saturday, that we cannot stop by our statue kill on the way to Ntov on Sunday because it would forfeit our turn? I just don't understand. Please explain.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The basica idea is its unfair to other guilds to abuse the longer rotational turn on Zone X, to allow you to kill Mob A also.  Once you begin your turn on a rotation, you should follow it through, and not use the fact that it is on rotation to allow you to get more mobs.<br>
<br>
When the Trakanon rotation was originally set up there was a rule on it, that is no longer applies, but it is a good example of the reasoning behind the current rule.  The rule was, if you were up for the Trakanon rotation, you could not race for VS that day.  You have to remember, the Trakanon rotation was started when the 2 most contested mobs on the server were Trak and VS, because they both dropped class armor (BP and legs respectivly).  <br>
<br>
So the general idea was, if you were garenteed a turn at killing Trakanon, you could not use this fact to allow you to race for VS.<br>
<br>
Today, that rule is no longer followed, but the spirit of the rule lives on in the rule you stated.<br>
<br>
If you are garenteed 3 days in VT without any outside disruption, then you should not abue this fact to allow you to get VT and other rotational mobs.  The same for NToV, you should not abuse the protection of the 2 days the rotation garentees you to go kill other mobs. <p><P><A HREF="http://www.jakefitch.com/asb/char_detail.asp?Name=Milambus" TARGET="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://jakefitch.com/sig/eq/sig1.jpg" HEIGHT="150" WIDTH="400" ALT="Milambus Mandragon" BORDER="0"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeshterdaggerfury>Jeshter Daggerfury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Spin Doctor <br>
