<br>
Part 1:<br>
<br>
On a multi-day zone Rotation, a guild may leave the zone and not be done with their &quot;turn&quot;. It's their &quot;turn&quot; for the amount of days said zone is allowed.<br>
<br>
Part 2:<br>
<br>
If you choose to be on a multi-day rotation, you are given the courtesy that no other guild/alliance will go in when you log for the night. The return from you (said guild/alliance) is that you give up any other Rotation Mob that you are up for, UNTIL you declare your 'turn' in the multiday zone over. <br>
<br>
Notice Part 2... once you start your &quot;turn&quot; on a multi-day Rotation, you give up all your other Rotation Mobs.  That is to say.. you cannot leave VT on day 2 of your 3 day rotation to kill KT and then go back in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nilasu>Nilasu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(5/16/03 1:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=342.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> OK, I just need a quick claraifcation:<br>
